                <change who="#admin" when="2021-11-02T14:17:45.617Z" type="general" xml:id="UT23703-167-017-6" source="tengyur-data-4104-4149_PH_new_v2.4.xml">
                    <desc>The text comprises chapter 3 (dhūtaguṇa) of Upatiśa's Vimuktimarga (T. 1648; Nj. 1293; K 968). Several versions of the text in other recensions of the
            Kangyur (N, C, Q, B) all contain an excessive passage that appears to be an erroneously inserted excerpt from Nāgārjuna's Sūtrasamuccaya (D 3934). The editors of the Derge recension appear
            to have excised the passage from their printing. Given the structural similarities between Upatiśa's Vimuktimarga and Buddhaghosa's Vissuddhimagga, Malalasekera considers Buddhaghosa's
            text to be a revised version of Upatiśa's.</desc>
                </change>
